The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Mesco to expand in Orissa 

 OUR CORRESPONDENT 

 Bhubaneswar, July 23: Mid-East Integrated Steels Ltd (Mesco) has expressed its intent to invest Rs 20,000 crore to expand its existing project at Duburi. Mesco chairman J.K. Singh yesterday submitted a proposal in this regard to chief minister Naveen Patnaik at his secretariat chamber. 

 In his proposal, Singh has suggested ramping up of the 1.5-million tonnes per annum Duburi plant to 7 mtpa by 2012. Stemcor, the UK-based trading house which is currently financing the groups steel project at Duburi, has agreed to bankroll its expansion as well. 

 Singh went along with Mathew Stock, managing director of Stemcor. Singh impressed upon Naveen that the company wished to complete its unfinished project at Kalinga Nagar. On his part, the chief minister assured the Mesco chairman of considering its proposal carefully. 




